===Verb===
{{en-verb|grows|growing|grew|grown|past2=growed|past2_qual=dialectal|past_ptc2=growed|past_ptc2_qual=dialectal}}

# {{lb|en|ergative}} To [[become]] [[larger]], to [[increase]] in [[magnitude]].
#: ''Children '''grow''' quickly.''
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[appear]] or [[sprout]].
#: ''Leaf buds '''grew''' on the trees with the advance of spring.''
#: ''A long tail began to '''grow''' from his backside.''
# {{lb|en|intransitive}} To [[develop]], to [[mature]].
#: ''As I '''grew''' throughout adolescence, I came to appreciate many things about human nature.''
# {{lb|en|transitive}} To cause or allow something to become bigger, especially to [[cultivate]] plants.
#* {{quote-journal|en|date=March 01, 2011|author=Peter Roff| title=Another Foolish Move By Congress| work=Fox News| url=http://www.foxnews.com/opinion/2011/03/01/foolish-congress/| passage=''The Bush administration – which sought to '''grow''' the number of fisheries managed under a program known as “catch shares”...''}}
